And the descendants of Montesuma are filled with militancy.
However, Mexico ' s relationship with more than 35 million Mexican Americans living in the United States is the most difficult.
You want to talk about resentments?
That's enough.
There are winners and losers in Mexico, people who find opportunities in that country, and those who don't.
In Los Angeles, Las Vegas, Phoenix, Denver or San Antonio, there are so many people of Mexican origin for just one reason: at some point in their family history, no one, father or grandfather, had the opportunity to realize himself in Mexico and had to go north.
Most of the time, they were Mexicans of a certain type - dark, poorly educated, from poor peasant families.
We're their descendants, and we remember that.
That's not what Mexico sees.
Today, our life is an expression of American dreams, and we went to good schools and did good work, but we can't forget that even this dream is American, not Mexican.
Our national self-determination is confusing and unclear, but we know which country we consider our own.
United States of America.
